SUMMARY

Researcher with a strong experience in organic synthesis of small drug-like molecules, antimicrobial biopolymer (polysaccharide) films, polymer characterizations, data analysis, and computational studies. Enjoys learning new skills, techniques and problem-solving. Highly motivated, creative, result-oriented team player with exceptional communication skills. Diligent, capable of meeting deadlines for multiple tasks, ensuring successful completion of project goals.
EDUCATION

    Ph.D. Chemistry from Pondicherry University, India (September 2016 – May 2023)
    MSc Chemistry (5-year integrated course) from the University of Hyderabad, India (2009-2014)

RESEARCH EXPERIENCE / WORK EXPERIENCE

    Doctoral research (September 2016 to May 2023, Dept. of Chemistry, Pondicherry University, India)
        Developed chitosan-based antimicrobial polymer films using small molecules with potential for industrial or medical applications.
        Assisted colleagues in in silico evaluation in drug-discovery against disease proteins.
        Mentored 7 graduate students in lab practices and oversaw their capstone projects.
    Master of Science in Chemistry dissertation (2014): University of Hyderabad, India.
        Developed emulsions of polyurethane-clay composites with improved physical properties.

SKILLS AND AREAS OF EXPOSURE

    Polymer synthesis, chemistry, and analysis
        Preparation of thin film membranes, chemical and physical characterization. Carbohydrate polymers / Biopolymers.
    Synthetic organic chemistry
        Small-molecule inhibitor design and synthesis.
        Reaction optimization via simple, cost-effective reagents.
    Instruments/techniques: Hands-on with Nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), Fourier transform-infrared (FTIR), Ultraviolet-Vis (UV-Vis) spectroscopy, Gel permeation chromatography (GPC), Thermogravimetric analysis (TGA), Differential scanning calorimetry (DSC), Tensile strength analysis. Limited experience with High Resolution-Transmission Electron Microscope (HR-TEM), High-performance liquid chromatography (HPLC), X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), X-ray diffraction (powder and single crystal XRD), and Electrospinning. Good Laboratory Practice (GLP)
    Computational skills
        Molecular docking and analysis using Autodock Vina and Autodock 4, Pymol, Ligplot+, Biovia Discovery studio, and PyRX. Use of BLAST studies, RAST annotation pipeline, WGCNA clustering, and Geochip analysis. Basic Linux, Python programming, and scriptwriting using Chemdraw, SciFinder, PubChem, Chemspider, Scifinder, Chemsketch, and MarvinSketch.
    Data analysis and interpretation
        GraphPad Prism, Origin, Microsoft Excel, and ImageJ software for data analysis and interpretation.

